'From Squeak 2.4b of April 23, 1999 on 30 April 1999 at 9:29:15 am'!"Change Set:		ThreeFixesDate:			30 April 1999Author:			Dan IngallsA fix to TextOnCurve that got broken by the faster type-in code.A fix to classComment: submitted by Mark Guzdial.A fix to FileDirectory fileExists: that makes filename matching be case-insensitive	with an override in UnixFileDirectory for case-sensitivity."!!FileDirectory methodsFor: 'testing' stamp: 'di 4/30/1999 09:24'!fileExists: filenameOrPath	"Answer true if a file of the given name exists. The given name may be either a full path name or a local file within this directory."	"FileDirectory default fileExists: Smalltalk sourcesName"	| fName dir |	FileDirectory splitName: filenameOrPath to:		[:filePath :name |			fName _ name.			filePath isEmpty				ifTrue: [dir _ self]				ifFalse: [dir _ FileDirectory on: filePath]].	dir fileNames do: [:thisName | (fName sameAs: thisName) ifTrue: [^ true]].	^ false! !!TextOnCurve methodsFor: 'as yet unclassified' stamp: 'di 4/30/1999 08:06'!composeAll	self composeLinesFrom: firstCharacterIndex		withLines: OrderedCollection new		atY: container top.! !!UnixFileDirectory methodsFor: 'file names' stamp: 'di 4/30/1999 09:27'!fileExists: filenameOrPath	"Overridden to implement case-sensitive fileName matching."	"FileDirectory default fileExists: Smalltalk sourcesName"	| fName dir |	FileDirectory splitName: filenameOrPath to:		[:filePath :name |			fName _ name.			filePath isEmpty				ifTrue: [dir _ self]				ifFalse: [dir _ FileDirectory on: filePath]].	dir fileNames do: [:thisName | (fName = thisName) ifTrue: [^ true]].	^ false! !